========,1,preface.
Westside Township is a township in Nobles County, Minnesota, United States.
The population was 258 at the 2000 census.
========,2,Geography.
According to the United States Census Bureau, the township has a total area of 35.3 square miles (91.4 km²), all of it land.
The main geographic feature of Westside Township is the Kanaranzi Creek which bisects the township from the northeast to southwest corners.
